<paragraph blockId="3.[151,527,153,215]" box="[151,302,189,215]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,294,189,215]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 10" captionStart-1="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId-0="3.[151,250,1624,1649]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,264,1921,1946]" captionTargetBox-0="[186,1404,832,1580]" captionTargetBox-1="[248,1346,178,1896]" captionTargetId-0="figure@3.[151,1436,828,1590]" captionTargetId-1="figure@4.[180,1407,166,1902]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionText-0="FIGURE 10. Flavoperla triangulata sp. n. (male). 10. Adult, dorsal view." captionText-1="FIGURES 11–18. Flavoperla triangulata sp. n. (male). 11. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. 12. Terminalia, dorsal view. 13. Sternum 9, ventral view. 14. Sternum 9, lateral view. 15. Aedeagus, ventral top view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, lateral view. 18. Aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3242502/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3242504/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Figs. 10–18</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,261,791]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,324,261,288]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Adult habitus.</emphasis>
General color yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[704,789,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1624,1649]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,832,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,828,1590]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 10. Flavoperla triangulata sp. n. (male). 10. Adult, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3242502/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Head mostly pale with a triangular brown marking between ocelli, and a smaller pale brown obscure area between frontoclypeus and M-line; compound eyes dark, ocelli with dark rings; antennae brown (
<figureCitation box="[536,674,333,359]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 10" captionStart-1="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId-0="3.[151,250,1624,1649]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,264,1921,1946]" captionTargetBox-0="[186,1404,832,1580]" captionTargetBox-1="[248,1346,178,1896]" captionTargetId-0="figure@3.[151,1436,828,1590]" captionTargetId-1="figure@4.[180,1407,166,1902]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionText-0="FIGURE 10. Flavoperla triangulata sp. n. (male). 10. Adult, dorsal view." captionText-1="FIGURES 11–18. Flavoperla triangulata sp. n. (male). 11. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. 12. Terminalia, dorsal view. 13. Sternum 9, ventral view. 14. Sternum 9, lateral view. 15. Aedeagus, ventral top view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, lateral view. 18. Aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3242502/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3242504/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Figs. 10–11</figureCitation>
). Pronotum brown, rectangular except lateral areas paler, with pale brown rugosities and a pair of brown lines along anterior and posterior margins (
<figureCitation box="[1089,1173,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1946]" captionTargetBox="[248,1346,178,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[180,1407,166,1902]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Flavoperla triangulata sp. n. (male). 11. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. 12. Terminalia, dorsal view. 13. Sternum 9, ventral view. 14. Sternum 9, lateral view. 15. Aedeagus, ventral top view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, lateral view. 18. Aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3242504/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Wings hyaline, veins brown; legs pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,261,791]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,442,468]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Male.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[420,558,441,468]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="8.9" metricValueMin="8.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" unit="mm" value="8.75" valueMax="8.9" valueMin="8.6">8.6–8.9 mm</quantity>
; forewing length 
<quantity box="[756,921,441,468]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.095" metricValueMax="1.1099999999999999" metricValueMin="1.08" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" unit="mm" value="10.95" valueMax="11.1" valueMin="10.8">10.8–11.1 mm</quantity>
; hindwing length 
<quantity box="[1124,1262,441,468]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.7" metricValueMax="9.8" metricValueMin="9.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" unit="mm" value="9.7" valueMax="9.8" valueMin="9.6">9.6–9.8 mm</quantity>
. Hammer basal half brown with wing-shaped anterolateral extensions; apical half mostly unpigmented; subapex distinctly tapering and nipple-like covered by numerous brown spinules; apex slightly swollen and turned upward in lateral view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1946]" captionTargetBox="[248,1346,178,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[180,1407,166,1902]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Flavoperla triangulata sp. n. (male). 11. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. 12. Terminalia, dorsal view. 13. Sternum 9, ventral view. 14. Sternum 9, lateral view. 15. Aedeagus, ventral top view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, lateral view. 18. Aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3242504/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Figs. 13–14</figureCitation>
). Sternum 9 sclerotized except medial portion membranous with broadly rounded apical process. Epiproct sclerite brown and subtriangular, divided into two small subtriangles by a slender and membranous band; anterior margin set between bases of paired dark brown triangular spines (
<figureCitation box="[901,985,621,647]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1946]" captionTargetBox="[248,1346,178,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[180,1407,166,1902]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Flavoperla triangulata sp. n. (male). 11. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. 12. Terminalia, dorsal view. 13. Sternum 9, ventral view. 14. Sternum 9, lateral view. 15. Aedeagus, ventral top view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, lateral view. 18. Aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3242504/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Paraprocts short, curved forward with small apical hooks (
<figureCitation box="[379,464,657,683]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1946]" captionTargetBox="[248,1346,178,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[180,1407,166,1902]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Flavoperla triangulata sp. n. (male). 11. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. 12. Terminalia, dorsal view. 13. Sternum 9, ventral view. 14. Sternum 9, lateral view. 15. Aedeagus, ventral top view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, lateral view. 18. Aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3242504/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Dorsum aedeagus with a pair of short vertical sclerites medially (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1314,657,684]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1946]" captionTargetBox="[248,1346,178,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[180,1407,166,1902]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Flavoperla triangulata sp. n. (male). 11. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. 12. Terminalia, dorsal view. 13. Sternum 9, ventral view. 14. Sternum 9, lateral view. 15. Aedeagus, ventral top view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, lateral view. 18. Aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3242504/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
), ventrally gourd-shaped and gradually tapering to an obtuse triangular tip with two rounded processes in basolateral area (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1946]" captionTargetBox="[248,1346,178,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[180,1407,166,1902]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Flavoperla triangulata sp. n. (male). 11. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. 12. Terminalia, dorsal view. 13. Sternum 9, ventral view. 14. Sternum 9, lateral view. 15. Aedeagus, ventral top view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, lateral view. 18. Aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3242504/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Figs. 13, 15</figureCitation>
), aedeagus curved upward in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[712,795,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1946]" captionTargetBox="[248,1346,178,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[180,1407,166,1902]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Flavoperla triangulata sp. n. (male). 11. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. 12. Terminalia, dorsal view. 13. Sternum 9, ventral view. 14. Sternum 9, lateral view. 15. Aedeagus, ventral top view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, lateral view. 18. Aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3242504/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
), in caudal view with a small “fish mouth-shaped mark” (
<figureCitation box="[160,243,765,791]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1946]" captionTargetBox="[248,1346,178,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[180,1407,166,1902]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Flavoperla triangulata sp. n. (male). 11. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. 12. Terminalia, dorsal view. 13. Sternum 9, ventral view. 14. Sternum 9, lateral view. 15. Aedeagus, ventral top view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, lateral view. 18. Aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3242504/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
